The paper proposes a reinforcement learning method to train an agent to suggest effective medical tests. This involves formulating the problem as a Markov decision process, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning techniques for training the agent suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the proposed method is in the field of healthcare, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as these fields often intersect with healthcare.
